JSON- Java Script Object Notation
Person={name : "Nisha", age:31, city:"Delhi"};

Person.name

Data type
a string
a number
an object
an array
a boolean
null


file type-- json
mime type-- "application/json"

JSOn vs XML
likes
- self describing
-values within values
- use with any other programming language
- can be fetched by ajax engine

Unlike
-json is text not tags
- json is shorter
-json can use array
- xml has be parsed with xml parser but json can be parsed by standard javasript function


JSOn Object syntax
{
"Person":{name : "Nisha", age:31, city:"Delhi"}

}

